# 🎨 Stable Diffusion Web UI

> A powerful, feature-rich browser interface for [Stable Diffusion](https://github.com/Stability-AI/stablediffusion), built on top of the [Gradio](https://gradio.app/) framework. Turn text descriptions into stunning images — or transform existing images — entirely from your browser, with no coding required.

---

## ✨ What Is This?

**Stable Diffusion Web UI** is an open-source front-end that wraps Stable Diffusion's AI image generation models in an easy-to-use web interface. Whether you want to generate images from a text prompt, edit existing images, upscale, inpaint, train custom styles, or call everything through a REST API, this project has you covered — right out of the box.

---

## 🚀 Key Features

- **Text-to-Image (txt2img)** — Generate images from natural language prompts with fine-grained control over sampling, steps, resolution, and seed
- **Image-to-Image (img2img)** — Feed an existing image + a prompt to guide transformations, including loopback and batch processing
- **Inpainting & Outpainting** — Erase and regenerate specific regions of an image, or extend it beyond its original borders
- **LoRA & Hypernetwork Support** — Load custom fine-tuned model adapters (LyCORIS, LoRA, HyperNetworks) directly from the UI
- **Checkpoint Merger** — Blend up to 3 model checkpoints together into a single new model without writing a line of code
- **Upscaling Suite** — Built-in upscalers: RealESRGAN, ESRGAN, SwinIR, Swin2SR, and LDSR for latent-space super resolution
- **Face Restoration** — Automatically fix faces using GFPGAN or CodeFormer
- **Textual Inversion** — Train and load custom text embeddings to inject concepts or styles into prompts
- **X/Y/Z Plot Grid** — Systematically compare any combination of parameters across a batch of generations
- **HighRes Fix** — Produce high-resolution images in a single click without common distortion artifacts
- **Prompt Editing & Attention Control** — Shift prompts mid-generation and weight individual tokens with `(keyword:1.5)` syntax
- **Full REST API** — Programmatically control everything via a FastAPI-backed HTTP API (`--api` flag)
- **Extension System** — Install community-built extensions from within the UI itself
- **Low-VRAM Modes** — `--medvram` and `--lowvram` flags make it viable on cards with as little as 4 GB (reported working on 2 GB)
- **xFormers Acceleration** — Optional memory-efficient attention via Facebook's xFormers library for significant speed gains

