## 🖥️ System Requirements & Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure your system meets the following requirements.

### Hardware

| Component | Minimum | Recommended |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| GPU VRAM  | 4 GB    | 8 GB+       |
| RAM       | 8 GB    | 16 GB+      |
| Storage   | 10 GB   | 20 GB+      |

> **CPU-only generation is possible** but extremely slow. A CUDA-capable NVIDIA GPU is strongly recommended.

### Software

| Dependency | Required Version | Notes |
|------------|-----------------|-------|
| **Python** | 3.10.6          | ⚠️ Specifically 3.10.6 — newer versions break PyTorch compatibility |
| **Git**    | Any recent      | Used to clone the repo and manage extensions |
| **CUDA Toolkit** | 11.8+ (NVIDIA) | Only needed for GPU acceleration |

> **macOS (Apple Silicon):** Python and Git via [Homebrew](https://brew.sh/) work fine. See the Apple Silicon section below.

