## ⚡ Installation — The Easy Way

Follow the instructions for your operating system. The launch scripts handle virtual environment creation, dependency installation, and model downloading automatically.

---

### 🪟 Windows (NVIDIA GPU)

**Option A — Release Package (Easiest, no Git needed)**

1. Download `sd.webui.zip` from the [v1.0.0-pre release](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/releases/tag/v1.0.0-pre).
2. Extract the zip to a folder of your choice (e.g., `C:\sd-webui`).
3. Run `update.bat` once to pull the latest code.
4. Run `run.bat` to launch.

**Option B — Git Clone (Recommended for staying up-to-date)**

```bat
:: Step 1 — Install Python 3.10.6 from https://python.org
:: ⚠️ Check "Add Python to PATH" during installation

:: Step 2 — Install Git from https://git-scm.com/download/win

:: Step 3 — Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui.git
cd stable-diffusion-webui

:: Step 4 — Launch (everything else is automatic)
webui-user.bat
```

The first launch will take several minutes as it downloads PyTorch, dependencies, and the default SD 1.5 model checkpoint.

