## 🔧 Configuration — `webui-user` File

No `.env` file is used. Instead, customize your launch by editing the platform-specific user config file **before** running the app.

**Windows:** Edit `webui-user.bat`

```bat
set PYTHON=                    :: Path to specific python binary (leave blank for auto-detect)
set GIT=                       :: Path to specific git binary
set VENV_DIR=                  :: Override virtual environment location
set COMMANDLINE_ARGS=          :: ← Put your launch flags here
```

**Linux / macOS:** Edit `webui-user.sh`

```bash
export COMMANDLINE_ARGS=""     # ← Put your launch flags here
export python_cmd="python3.10" # Optionally specify Python version
```

### Common Launch Flags

Add these to `COMMANDLINE_ARGS`:

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--medvram` | Reduces VRAM usage with a slight speed penalty. Use for 4–6 GB cards. |
| `--lowvram` | Aggressively reduces VRAM; very slow but works on 2–3 GB cards. |
| `--xformers` | Enables xFormers attention for faster generation on supported NVIDIA cards. |
| `--api` | Enables the REST API alongside the Web UI (accessible at `/docs`). |
| `--listen` | Exposes the UI on your local network (binds to `0.0.0.0`). |
| `--port 8080` | Launches on a custom port (default: `7860`). |
| `--share` | Creates a public Gradio tunnel URL (useful for Colab / remote access). |
| `--no-half` | Disables float16 precision. Use if you see black or corrupted images. |
| `--autolaunch` | Automatically opens the browser when the server starts. |
| `--theme dark` | Forces dark or light theme (`dark` / `light`). |

**Example `webui-user.sh` for a 6 GB NVIDIA card:**

```bash
export COMMANDLINE_ARGS="--medvram --xformers --autolaunch"
```

